                     <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" key="work_292">Mujmal al-ḥikmah</title>
                     <title xml:lang="ar" key="work_292">مجمل الحكمة</title>
                     <note>Lacks the beginning of the preface and breaks off in the ninth section of the tenth risala of the third qism. A philosophical compendium, consisting of a much abbreviated translation of the Rasa'il of the Ikhwan al-Safa. Headings in red. Some pages on pink or green paper. The tranlator informs us that he undertook the task at the instance of Sayyid Baha al-Din Saif al-Muluk, one of the close companions (khawass) of Amir Timur.</note>
                     <incipit>... shari'at-i khuday-ra ashkara kardand</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Ethe, No. 2225.</bibl>
                        <bibl>Price's bequest is noted in the Journal for 1836, pp. xii-xiv (an obituary notice p. lx).</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
